12x\equiv9\pmod{15}
\gcd(12,15)=3
3
15=12\times1+3\\ 3=15-12\times 1\\ 3=15+2\times(-1)\\ \implies9=15\times3+12\times(-3)\\ \implies12\times(-3)\equiv9\pmod{15}
x\equiv-3\pmod{15}
\begin{eqnarray}{\bf Hint}\quad 12x\equiv 9\!\!\!\pmod{15} &\iff& 15\mid 12x-9\\ &\iff& \dfrac{12x-9^{\phantom I}}{15} = \dfrac{4x-3}5\in\Bbb Z\\ \\ &\iff& 5\mid 4x-3\\ \\ &\iff& 4x\equiv3\!\!\!\pmod 5 \end{eqnarray}
\,{\rm mod}\ 5\!:\,\ 3 \equiv 4x\equiv -x\ \Rightarrow\ x \equiv -3\equiv 2\ 
\ x = 2 + 5n = \ldots,-3,2,7,12,17\ldots  \equiv\, 2,7,12\!\!\pmod{15}
12x\equiv 9 \pmod{15}
4x\equiv 3\pmod{5}
